Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum racked up 33 points, nine assists, and eight rebounds to lift the Boston Celtics to a 118-115 win over the Minnesota Timberwolves.
Others: Derrick White scored 26 points for Boston, while Sam Hauser — filling in for the injured Jaylen Brown — hit five three-pointers and scored 15 points. Julius Randle led Minnesota with 27 points, eight rebounds and seven assists. Naz Reid added 20 points off the bench, while Jaden McDaniels had 19 points and eight boards.
